Print the number of products in the ArrayList using the size method:
java
Copy code
System.out.println(products.size() + " products can be found in the list.");
The code demonstrates various operations on the ArrayList, such as adding, removing, setting, and accessing elements. It also showcases the usage of the Product class, which represents a product in the web shop application.
